sentences: Maria Dolores Malumbres Carranza (11 April 1931 – 5 January 2019) was a Spanish pianist, music educator and composer.
She first studied music with her violinist father Jose Luis Malumbres and in Cordoba in 1948.
From 1984-87 she taught harmony and analysis at the Music Conservatory of Logroño.
She began to compose in 1953, and the next year premiered her String Quartet.
